            "summary": "The global Milled Carbon Fiber Market is set to grow significantly, with a projected increase from USD 182 million in 2024 to USD 302 million by 2029, at a CAGR of 10.8%. The rise in demand is attributed to the unique properties and increased applications of milled carbon fiber. Key industries benefiting from this growth include automotive and electrical & electronics, where the material enhances efficiency and sustainability. Technological advancements in manufacturing processes are also contributing to the market's expansion, creating high-quality, vibrant, and durable milled carbon fiber products. Major players in the market include Toray Industries, Mitsubishi Chemical Group, and Teijin Limited. Key drivers include the development of eco-friendly milled carbon fiber from recycled composites, while challenges involve competition from low-cost alternatives. The market is poised to benefit from opportunities arising in emerging markets despite challenges such as the lack of availability of composite materials.",
